analysisPopulations.name: Entered Population
analysisPopulations.label: Entered
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who sign the informed consent form

analysisPopulations.name: Enrolled/Intent-to-Treat Population
analysisPopulations.label: ITT
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who receive at least 1 dose of study drug
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Efficacy Population
analysisPopulations.label: Efficacy
analysisPopulations.description: All participants with evaluable disease per their baseline assessment and at least 1 complete postbaseline assessment
analysisPopulations.criteria: Evaluable disease at baseline and at least 1 complete postbaseline assessment

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Population
analysisPopulations.label: Safety
analysisPopulations.description: All participants who take at least 1 dose of study drug. The safety population will be used for all analyses of dosing, exposure, and safety.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Population
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.description: All treated participants who receive at least 1 dose of study drug and have at least 1 evaluable PK sample
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least 1 dose of study drug and have at least 1 evaluable PK sample

characteristics.description: Eastern Cooperation Oncology Group Performance Status at baseline

characteristics.name: Pathological Diagnosis Type

characteristics.name: Histopathological Diagnosis Grade
characteristics.description: Histopathological diagnosis grade at study entry

characteristics.name: Prior Cancer Therapies

characteristics.name: Historical Illness
characteristics.description: Historical illness by MedDRA preferred term, including infusion-related reaction and hypersensitivity
